erial and exploring films from a historical perspective. The guide's focus is on good research practice, whether it be conducting an interview, visiting an archive, undertaking textual analysis or defining a research question.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aMotion picturesxResearchxMethodology. 7aPERFORMING ARTS / Film & Video / History & Criticism.2bisacsh  aArchive.  aFilm.  aHistory.  aResearch.  aSources.  aStudy guide.1 aBarber, Sian, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 2015 eBook-Packagez978311128311140uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978071909875840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780719098758423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780719098758/original  a978-3-11-128311-1  Manchester University Press 2015 eBook-Packageb2015  aGBV-deGruyter-alles